One of the most beautiful and largest parks in Paris, unknown to visitors to the city from outside France The garden is large, clean, and has more than one lake. You can do many activities, including sports, art, food, and a zoo. Entrance is free, and indeed the best time to visit this garden is in the morning and in the spring and summer seasons. If you love nature and would like to take a quiet period, you are in the right place.
